00:02:57.891 --> 00:02:58.727
But you might be saying,

00:02:58.727 --> 00:03:00.662
well, why can't I pick a value of k

00:03:00.662 --> 00:03:03.981
that makes the derivative undefined?

00:03:03.981 --> 00:03:05.914
And so, you can think of what that is,

00:03:05.914 --> 00:03:07.271
what would make undefined,

00:03:07.271 --> 00:03:09.900
well, if 25 plus five k is equal to zero,

00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:11.448
well, then this is going to be,

00:03:11.448 --> 00:03:13.170
you're gonna have zero squared,

00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:14.051
and divide it by zero,

00:03:14.051 --> 00:03:15.296
it's going to be undefined,

00:03:15.296 --> 00:03:19.817
so you could say f prime of negative five

00:03:19.817 --> 00:03:21.733
undefined,

00:03:21.733 --> 00:03:26.098
undefined if k is equal to what?

00:03:26.098 --> 00:03:28.413
Negative five, right?

00:03:28.413 --> 00:03:31.207
Five times negative five plus 25 is zero,

00:03:31.207 --> 00:03:32.306
but this,

00:03:32.306 --> 00:03:34.825
if k is equal to negative five,

00:03:34.825 --> 00:03:37.593
then this can't be a
critical point anymore,

00:03:37.593 --> 00:03:39.641
x equals negative five
can't be a critical point

00:03:39.641 --> 00:03:42.070
because it won't be in
it's domain anymore.

00:03:42.070 --> 00:03:43.779
If k is equal to negative five,

00:03:43.779 --> 00:03:45.980
then f of x would be equal to one

00:03:45.980 --> 00:03:50.120
over x squared plus five x,

00:03:50.120 --> 00:03:51.215
plus five x,

00:03:51.215 --> 00:03:54.368
and then f will not be
defined at negative five,

00:03:54.368 --> 00:03:56.123
and so the negative five
couldn't be a critical point

00:03:56.123 --> 00:03:58.808
because it's not even in the domain.

00:03:58.808 --> 00:04:00.238
So the important thing is,

00:04:00.238 --> 00:04:01.585
in order to be a critical point,

00:04:01.585 --> 00:04:02.987
it has to be in the domain,

00:04:02.987 --> 00:04:05.086
and the derivative at that point

00:04:05.086 --> 00:04:07.130
has to be equal to zero undefined.

00:04:07.130 --> 00:04:09.712
I can get the derivative to
be undefined at negative five,

00:04:09.712 --> 00:04:11.505
if we said k equals negative five,

00:04:11.505 --> 00:04:13.402
but with we said k equals negative five,

00:04:13.402 --> 00:04:16.928
then x equals negative five
will no longer be in the domain,

00:04:16.928 --> 00:04:20.068
so we wanna go with the k
that just makes the numerator

00:04:20.068 --> 00:04:21.582
of our derivative equal to zero,

00:04:21.582 --> 00:04:24.628
or sets our entire
derivative equal to zero.

